import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

X=[]
ims=[]
for i in range(0,15):
    img = cv2.imread(os.path.join(img_path,img_list[i]))
    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    
    ims.append(img)
    im=np.array(img)
    X.append(im)
    plt.imshow(img)
    plt.show()
X=np.array(X)

#We will generate data using data generator
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
#Building a training set generator
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255,shear_range=0.2,zoom_range=0.2,horizontal_flip=True,validation_split=0.2)
training_set = train_datagen.flow_from_directory('Cars Images',subset='training',target_size=(128,128),batch_size=32,class_mode='categorical',shuffle=True)

Found 15 images belonging to 15 classes.

Now the training set is ready to be used by the team

Problems Faced¶

1. cv2 module reads image in BGR format but we need to display in RGB format. So we need to convert from BGR to RGB format.¶

2. all the images were of different shape , so we need to resize the images all with the same size of (128,128,3)¶

3 . for different cars we need to assign labels , to distingusih the make of the car .¶
